==English==
===Etymology===
First recorded in the sixteenth century; but compare [[w:Cicero|Cicero]], ''De Officiis'' I.xxii: ''cedant arma togae'' ‘arms yield to persuasion’.

===Proverb===
'''[[the]] [[pen]] [[is]] [[mightier]] [[than]] the [[sword]]'''
# More influence and power can be usurped by [[writing]] than by [[fighting]].

